<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12006f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12006f">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12006f"> 6(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> roches ecriantes / slithering</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Il y en a sur lesquelles il suffit que les jeunes filles aillent s&apos;asseoir et se laissent glisser pour &ecirc;tre certaines de trouver, dans les douze mois qui suivront le mari de leurs r&ecirc;ves. Les pierres qui, &agrave; St-Aubin- du-Cormier, &agrave; Montault (Ille-et-Vilaine) et ailleurs, comblent ainsi les v&oelig;ux les plus chers des jouvencelles, conservent pour ce motif le nom de <mark>roches &eacute;criantes</mark>, du vieux mot fran&ccedil;ais: &eacute;crier, qui signifie <mark>glisser</mark>. <br><font color="green">[There are some which young girls have only to sit on and let themselves slide down in order to be certain of finding, within the following twelve months, the husband of their dreams. The rocks at St-Aubin-du-Cormier, Montault (Ille-et-Vilaine), and elsewhere, that in this way fulfil these lasses&apos; dearest wishes, are still called &lsquo;<i>roches &eacute;criantes</i>&rsquo;, from the old French word &lsquo;<i>&eacute;crier</i>&rsquo;, which means to slide.]</font> <small> l'Abb&eacute; A. Millon, <a name="AMPB" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#AMPB"><cite title="source">Pauvres Pierres! Les Megalithes Bretons devant la science</cite></a> (n.d) 19-20</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
